definition.value: A monocarboxylic acid that is 3-phenylpropionic acid in which the hydrogens at positions 2 and 5 of the phenyl ring are replaced by methoxy groups.
A monocarboxylic acid that is butanoic acid substituted by a phenyl group at position 3.
An  oxo dicarboxylic acid that consists of 4-hydroxycyclohexa-2,5-diene-1-carboxylic acid substituted by a 2-carboxy-2-oxoethyl group at position 1.
A hydroxynitrile that is phenylacetonitrile substituted by a hydroxy group at position 4.
An aminosulfinic acid comprising ethylamine having the sulfo group at the 2-position.
